{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab In a Group Simple Contest (see below), your GM may declare that both contestants suffer a Marginal Defeat to indicate that, although their results cancel out with respect to each other, their situation worsens compared to other contestants.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 5.2 Group Simple Contest\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In the Group Simple Contest, multiple participants take part in a simple contest. Each of you in your group conducts an individual simple contest against the GM, and the results for each side are collated to determine the victor.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A Group Simple Contest may pit all of you against a single resistance, representing one obstacle. Alternatively, a group simple contest may be a series of paired match-ups between two groups of contestants. If you are forced to participate in more than one contest, then you face the standard multiple opponent penalties.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 5.2.1 Procedure\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Your GM frames the contest.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab You choose a tactic, and figure your PC\u8217's target number (TN) using the ability rating and any modifiers. Your TN is the rating of their ability, plus or minus modifiers the GM may give you.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab Your GM determines the resistance. If two PCs contend, your opponent figures their TN as described in step 2.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab For each of your group, roll a d20 to determine your degree of success or failure, then apply any bumps. Your GM does the same for the resistance. Compare your rolled number with your TN to see how well you succeeded or failed with your ability. Remember to apply any bumps from masteries or hero points.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Determine the number of RPs scored by the victor in the contest from the Group Simple Contest Results table. On a tie the victory goes to the Better Roll.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Sum the RPs gained for each side.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 7.\tx360\tab The side with the highest number of RP is the victor in the contest.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab [Option] Determine Degee of Succes based on the difference between the winner and loser\u8217's resource point totals on the Group Simple Contest results table.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab [Option] Determine Benefits of Victory or Consequences of Defeat.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 8.\tx360\tab Describe the result based on the agreed prize.\sa180\par}
